Variables

To define variables we can use long names and numbers but name
has too start from a letter. We can't use special signs
for variables names.

message="that's very interesting point sir"
n=123
pi=3.145
twelve="why,what,where?"

type(n)
<class 'int'>

type(pi)
<class 'float'>

type(twelve)
<class 'str'>

type(message)
<class 'str'>

Keywords

Python has thirty three keywords

and-logic operator which returns True if only both values are true.

as - as is used to create an alias while importing a module

assert - is used for debugging purpose.
break - is used inside FOR and WHILE loops. BREAK will end small loop in its flows to the statment below the loop
